我往他身上吐口水是为了阻止中风。

966
00:47:19,829 --> 00:47:22,432
Oh. You just spit into him.
哦。你只是往他身上吐口水。

967
00:47:22,465 --> 00:47:24,400
Oh, that's a whole other ball game.
哦，那完全是另一回事了。

968
00:47:24,434 --> 00:47:27,303
Well, if I didn't, he would have had a lot of brain damage.
嗯，如果我不那么做，他会有严重的脑损伤。

969
00:47:27,336 --> 00:47:28,905
How old are you?
你多大了？

970
00:47:31,007 --> 00:47:32,508
A little older than you.
比你大一点。

971
00:47:32,542 --> 00:47:35,111
So people can only be around you for, like, what--
所以人们只能在你身边待，比如，什么——

972
00:47:35,144 --> 00:47:36,345
a year or something?
一年左右？

973
00:47:36,379 --> 00:47:38,247
No, I could go around seven years
不，我可以待七年左右

974
00:47:38,281 --> 00:47:40,283
without them expecting me to look older.
而不让他们期望我看起来变老。

975
00:47:40,316 --> 00:47:43,820
And I would've stayed with you for as long as possible.
我会尽可能长时间地和你在一起。

976
00:47:43,853 --> 00:47:45,788
But when you became one of the student leaders,
但当你成为学生领袖之一时，

977
00:47:45,822 --> 00:47:48,558
people on the street recognized you.
街上的人都认出你了。

978
00:47:48,591 --> 00:47:51,961
I thought, "This is his time."
我想，“这是他的时代。”

979
00:47:51,994 --> 00:47:55,498
You could have your choice of any woman out there.
你可以选择任何外面的女人。

980
00:47:55,531 --> 00:47:57,467
It didn't seem right to rob you of the chance
剥夺你遇见某个了不起的人的机会

981
00:47:57,500 --> 00:47:59,368
to meet someone amazing.
似乎是不对的。

982
00:48:01,170 --> 00:48:03,840
And you did, didn't you?
你确实遇到了，不是吗？

983
00:48:03,873 --> 00:48:06,342
I did. I really did.
是的。我确实遇到了。

984
00:48:06,375 --> 00:48:08,111
And you know what? I really should check
你知道吗？我真的应该查查

985
00:48:08,144 --> 00:48:10,113
and see how she's doing.
看看她怎么样了。

986
00:48:10,146 --> 00:48:11,490
And I gotta tell you something else.
我还要告诉你别的事。

987
00:48:11,514 --> 00:48:14,417
I feel like I'm really, like, tripping right now.
我觉得我现在真的，像是，有点懵。

988
00:48:14,450 --> 00:48:16,853
Am I gonna see you again?
我还会再见到你吗？

989
00:48:16,886 --> 00:48:19,088
Uh...
呃…

990
00:48:19,122 --> 00:48:21,524
of course, yeah.
当然，是的。

991
00:49:18,581 --> 00:49:20,883
Okay, this is Germany before World War II.
好的，这是二战前的德国。

992
00:49:20,917 --> 00:49:23,052
The sleepwalker keeps murdering people,
梦游者不停地杀人，

993
00:49:23,085 --> 00:49:25,221
but only because the evil guy has him under a spell.
但这只是因为那个邪恶的家伙用咒语控制了他。

994
00:49:25,254 --> 00:49:27,423
What does that remind you of?
这让你想起了什么？

995
00:49:28,491 --> 00:49:30,226
I'm flummoxed.
我被难住了。

996
00:49:30,259 --> 00:49:32,995
Germany? Evil spell?
德国？邪恶咒语？

997
00:49:33,029 --> 00:49:34,397
Adolf?
阿道夫？

998
00:49:34,430 --> 00:49:36,199
Your eyes remind me of somebody.
你的眼睛让我想起了某个人。

999
00:49:36,232 --> 00:49:38,100
Adolf Hitler.
阿道夫·希特勒。

1000
00:49:38,134 --> 00:49:40,069
No, that wasn't who I was thinking of.
不，那不是我想到的人。

1001
00:49:40,102 --> 00:49:43,072
Audrey Hepburn. Same initials, though.
奥黛丽·赫本。不过首字母缩写一样。

1002
00:49:43,105 --> 00:49:45,942
Can you please just focus on symbolism?
你能请你专注于象征意义吗？

1003
00:49:45,975 --> 00:49:47,910
Sorry.
抱歉。

1004
00:49:49,078 --> 00:49:51,013
Can I be under your spell?
我能被你的咒语控制吗？

1005
00:49:51,047 --> 00:49:52,915
Or better still, you could be under my spell.
或者更好的是，你可以被我的咒语控制。

1006
00:49:52,949 --> 00:49:54,517
What are you gonna make me do?
你要让我做什么？

1007
00:49:54,550 --> 00:49:56,652
Laugh hysterically.
歇斯底里地大笑。

1008
00:50:18,174 --> 00:50:21,043
Holy shit.
我的天。

1009
00:50:21,077 --> 00:50:23,546
Has it ever been like that for your before?
以前有过这样的感觉吗？

1010
00:50:23,579 --> 00:50:25,681
Not since the '80s.
80年代以后就没这样了。

1011
00:50:35,424 --> 00:50:37,126
Hey, where are you going?
嘿，你去哪儿？

1012
00:50:37,159 --> 00:50:38,327
Um, I've got an early class.
嗯，我有个早课。

1013
00:50:38,361 --> 00:50:40,096
