Every A-lister in New York will be there.
纽约的每个A级名流都会在那里。

1213
01:01:16,999 --> 01:01:18,834
You can have whoever you want.
你可以拥有任何你想要的人。

1214
01:01:18,867 --> 01:01:20,869
Mm. You get tired of that.
嗯。你会厌倦那个的。

1215
01:01:22,738 --> 01:01:24,306
Oh, I like this song.
哦，我喜欢这首歌。

1216
01:01:24,339 --> 01:01:25,874
You wanna dance. Yeah, do you?
你想跳舞。是的，你呢？

1217
01:01:25,908 --> 01:01:27,776
Yeah. Okay.
是的。好的。

1218
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:35,317
Aren't you gonna dance?
你不跳舞吗？

1219
01:01:35,350 --> 01:01:36,685
Me? I don't think so.
我？我想我不跳。

1220
01:01:36,718 --> 01:01:39,788
I'm not very good, no. Yes, you are.
我不太擅长，不。是的，你很擅长。

1221
01:01:39,821 --> 01:01:41,790
I remember. Yeah, but I don't remember.
我记得。是的，但我不记得了。

1222
01:01:50,799 --> 01:01:54,670
Do you sleep with henchmen?
你和手下睡觉吗？

1223
01:02:22,197 --> 01:02:24,299
Joey had to go. His dad is bugging out.
乔伊得走了。他爸爸快抓狂了。

1224
01:02:24,333 --> 01:02:26,134
Problems at work, no doubt.
工作上的问题，毫无疑问。

1225
01:02:27,970 --> 01:02:29,705
Hmm. Wonder who that could be.
嗯。想知道那会是谁。

1226
01:02:29,738 --> 01:02:31,974
Oh, isn't it insane?
哦，这不是很疯狂吗？

1227
01:02:32,007 --> 01:02:33,809
I was dating for 25 years
我约会了25年

1228
01:02:33,842 --> 01:02:36,878
and I've never imagined to feel this way about somebody.
我从未想象过对某人会有这种感觉。

1229
01:02:36,912 --> 01:02:38,714
What about you and Danny?
你和丹尼呢？

1230
01:02:38,747 --> 01:02:40,916
Mm, I never stopped loving him.
嗯，我从未停止爱他。

1231
01:02:40,949 --> 01:02:43,952
But his wife's sick so there's no even thinking about it.
但他妻子病了，所以甚至不用想了。

1232
01:02:43,986 --> 01:02:45,787
I'm just happy around him.
我只是在他身边很开心。

1233
01:02:45,821 --> 01:02:47,356
Reminds me of being hopeful.
让我想起了充满希望的感觉。

1234
01:02:47,389 --> 01:02:49,992
But how great would it be if we both had relationships?
但如果我们都有了关系那该多好？

1235
01:02:50,025 --> 01:02:51,860
I mean, wouldn't it be so cool--
我的意思是，那不是很酷吗——

1236
01:02:51,893 --> 01:02:53,228
Mott Street.
莫特街。

1237
01:02:53,261 --> 01:02:55,263
Mott Street. Oh!
莫特街。哦！

1238
01:02:55,297 --> 01:02:57,032
What is she doing back so soon?
她怎么这么快就回来了？

1239
01:02:57,065 --> 01:02:58,767
I guess things didn't work out with Diego.
我想和迭戈的事情没成。

1240
01:02:58,800 --> 01:03:00,035
Ugh. She's in Chinatown.
呃。她在唐人街。

1241
01:03:00,068 --> 01:03:02,437
God, just when things were going so well.
天哪，就在事情进展得这么顺利的时候。

1242
01:03:04,206 --> 01:03:06,808
Mm.
嗯。

1243
01:03:06,842 --> 01:03:08,844
Oh-- oh, God.
哦——哦，天哪。

1244
01:03:10,278 --> 01:03:12,881
I've never seen real dead people.
我从未见过真正的死人。

1245
01:03:12,914 --> 01:03:14,149
What did you do?
你做了什么？

1246
01:03:14,182 --> 01:03:15,917
You know how it is
你知道吃中餐是怎么回事

1247
01:03:15,951 --> 01:03:18,320
when you eat Chinese.
的时候。

1248
01:03:18,353 --> 01:03:20,889
Half an hour later you're hungry again.
半小时后你又饿了。

1249
01:03:20,922 --> 01:03:22,791
How could you?
你怎么能？

1250
01:03:24,359 --> 01:03:26,862
Oh, I just can't stop eating.
哦，我就是停不下来吃。

1251
01:03:26,895 --> 01:03:28,263
I'm so depressed.
我太沮丧了。

1252
01:03:28,296 --> 01:03:30,732
Why didn't he like me?
他为什么不喜欢我？

1253
01:03:30,766 --> 01:03:33,835
I am so much more bomb-ass than his girlfriend.
我比他女朋友酷多了。

1254
01:03:33,869 --> 01:03:36,204
Maybe she wasn't a homicidal maniac.
也许她不是个杀人狂。

1255
01:03:36,238 --> 01:03:37,472
Maybe.
也许吧。

1256
01:03:37,506 --> 01:03:39,908
This is disgusting!
这太恶心了！

1257
01:03:39,941 --> 01:03:41,076
I know.
我知道。

1258
01:03:41,109 --> 01:03:43,779
I could so easily hate myself.
我很容易恨自己。

1259
01:03:43,812 --> 01:03:46,915
But just because you overdid it one day,
但仅仅因为你有一天过度放纵了，

1260
01:03:46,948 --> 01:03:49,751
doesn't mean you have to be bad all weekend.
不意味着你整个周末都必须是坏的。

1261
01:03:49,785 --> 01:03:51,262
What's wrong with him?
他怎么了？

1262
01:03:52,821 --> 01:03:54,956
Finish him off, will ya?
解决他，好吗？

1263
01:03:57,793 --> 01:04:00,328
I said kill him.
我说杀了他。

1264
01:04:11,807 --> 01:04:14,776
You really can't kill.
你真的不能杀人。

1265
01:04:14,810 --> 01:04:18,013
You guys are so useless.
你们太没用了。

1266
01:04:18,046 --> 01:04:19,848
Forget it.
算了。

1267
01:04:21,249 --> 01:04:24,753
Hey, can I have a fortune cookie, at least?
嘿，我至少能吃个幸运饼干吗？

1268
01:04:36,998 --> 01:04:39,468
That was way too close.
那太接近了。

1269
01:04:39,501 --> 01:04:41,002
And I didn't put in rollers.
我还没上卷发器。

1270
01:04:41,036 --> 01:04:42,537
I'm gonna have coffin hair tomorrow.
明天我的头发会是棺材头。

1271
01:04:42,571 --> 01:04:44,239
I know.
我知道。

1272
01:04:44,272 --> 01:04:45,941
Goody, I don't think
古蒂，我觉得

1273
01:04:45,974 --> 01:04:47,976
I can do anything like that again.
我再也做不了那样的事了。

1274
01:04:48,009 --> 01:04:49,478
Me either.
我也是。

1275
01:04:56,551 --> 01:04:59,354
The world changes, we have to adapt.
世界在变，我们必须适应。

1276
01:04:59,387 --> 01:05:01,256
These violent old ways
这些暴力的旧方式

1277
01:05:01,289 --> 01:05:03,058
don't make any sense anymore.
不再有任何意义了。

1278
01:05:03,091 --> 01:05:05,360
But she won't listen.
但她不会听。

1279
01:05:05,393 --> 01:05:08,964
She's insane. Oh, tell me about it.
她疯了。哦，跟我说说吧。

1280
01:05:11,066 --> 01:05:13,435
Tepish, is there anything like a...
泰皮什，有没有像…

1281
01:05:13,468 --> 01:05:15,303
Sanguine's doctor?
嗜血者医生？

1282
01:05:15,337 --> 01:05:16,905
Stacy is sick.
斯泰茜病了。

1283
01:05:16,938 --> 01:05:18,840
That's impossible. We don't get sick.
那不可能。我们不会生病。

1284
01:05:18,874 --> 01:05:19,774
That's what I thought,
我也是这么想的，

1285
01:05:19,808 --> 01:05:22,210
but every night when we get up, she vomits.
但每晚我们起来时，她都会呕吐。

1286
01:05:22,244 --> 01:05:25,180
Just how old was she when she was awakened?
她被唤醒时到底多大？

1287
01:05:25,213 --> 01:05:26,915
20.
20岁。

1288
01:05:26,948 --> 01:05:28,483
And I assume there is a boyfriend.
我假设有个男朋友。

1289
01:05:28,517 --> 01:05:30,185
Why?
为什么？

1290
01:05:30,218 --> 01:05:32,254
She's not sick. She's pregnant.
她没病。她怀孕了。

1291
01:05:32,287 --> 01:05:34,422
So she can have a baby?
所以她能生孩子？

1292
01:05:34,456 --> 01:05:37,392
No, the pregnancy will end by itself.
不，怀孕会自行结束。

1293
01:05:37,425 --> 01:05:39,427
Unless she turns back.
除非她变回去。

1294
01:05:39,461 --> 01:05:41,930
Like, if Cisserus dies?
比如，如果西瑟勒斯死了？

1295
01:05:41,963 --> 01:05:44,332
Cisserus.
西瑟勒斯。

1296
01:05:44,366 --> 01:05:47,035
Don't you worry, hmm?
别担心，嗯？

1297
01:05:47,068 --> 01:05:50,105
Stacy will be just fine in about a week.
斯泰茜大约一周后就会没事的。

1298
01:05:51,406 --> 01:05:53,909
They notified us about a patient having seizures
他们通知我们一个癫痫发作的病人

1299
01:05:53,942 --> 01:05:55,987
who had a double puncture wound. When I asked who checked him in,
身上有双重穿刺伤。当我问是谁给他办理入院时，

1300
01:05:56,011 --> 01:05:58,180
I went back to their surveillance cameras.
我回去看了他们的监控录像。

1301
01:05:58,213 --> 01:06:00,048
Where's the body? Mount Sinai.
尸体在哪儿？西奈山医院。

1302
01:06:00,081 --> 01:06:02,617
Tell them we're coming. Mm-hmm.
告诉他们我们要来了。嗯哼。

1303
01:06:02,651 --> 01:06:06,621
All right, sit down, listen to me.
好了，坐下，听我说。

1304
01:06:07,923 --> 01:06:09,591
Now, I know you think I'm crazy,
现在，我知道你觉得我疯了，

1305
01:06:09,624 --> 01:06:12,460
but you have to do something for me.
但你必须为我做件事。

1306
01:06:12,494 --> 01:06:13,628
Sure.
当然。

1307
01:06:13,662 --> 01:06:15,664
Carry this with you at all times.
随时带着这个。

1308
01:06:15,697 --> 01:06:18,667
What? This is how you load it.
什么？这是装弹的方式。

1309
01:06:18,700 --> 01:06:20,902
Only use the silver bullets.
只用银子弹。

1310
01:06:20,936 --> 01:06:22,604
Only use them on what? Stacy?
只对什么用？斯泰茜？

1311
01:06:22,637 --> 01:06:24,439
Just keep it with you.
就带着它。

1312
01:06:24,472 --> 01:06:26,942
Don't give me any shit.
别跟我废话。

1313
01:06:26,975 --> 01:06:31,012
When a problem comes along, like hunger, you must whip it.
当问题来临时，比如饥饿，你必须鞭打它。

1314
01:06:31,046 --> 01:06:34,082
It says this guy's a comic? He's not even funny.
它说这家伙是个喜剧演员？他一点都不好笑。

1315
01:06:34,115 --> 01:06:35,517
I've never seen him in anything.
我从没在任何东西里见过他。

1316
01:06:35,550 --> 01:06:37,185
What's on?
放什么呢？

1317
01:06:37,219 --> 01:06:39,521
"Assholes Insult People More Talented Than Them."
“混蛋们侮辱比他们更有才华的人。”

1318
01:06:39,554 --> 01:06:43,058
"The Excessively '80s Countdown."
“过度80年代倒计时。”

1319
01:06:43,091 --> 01:06:44,326
Oh, show Goody.
哦，给古蒂看。

1320
01:06:44,359 --> 01:06:45,961
Oh.
哦。

1321
01:06:45,994 --> 01:06:49,564
So my father decided to give me this.
所以我父亲决定给我这个。

1322
01:06:49,598 --> 01:06:51,166
Hmm. That's weird.
嗯。真奇怪。

1323
01:06:51,199 --> 01:06:52,543
Oh, careful. It's got silver bullets in it.
哦，小心。里面有银子弹。

1324
01:06:54,302 --> 01:06:56,538
What's he thinking?
他在想什么？

1325
01:06:56,571 --> 01:06:58,473
He's got more paranoid
他变得更偏执了

1326
01:06:58,506 --> 01:07:00,084
since he saw the footage from the hospital.
自从他看了医院的录像。

1327
01:07:00,108 --> 01:07:01,977
What footage?
什么录像？

1328
01:07:02,010 --> 01:07:05,046
This guy just seemed to fly from a cab to the front door.
这家伙似乎直接从出租车飞到了前门。

1329
01:07:05,080 --> 01:07:06,581
I'm such an idiot.
我真是个白痴。

1330
01:07:06,615 --> 01:07:08,984
Why didn't I look for surveillance cameras?
我为什么没找监控摄像头？

1331
01:07:09,017 --> 01:07:10,995
Wait a minute, you-- No, no. We didn't do anything.
等等，你——不，不。我们没做什么。

1332
01:07:11,019 --> 01:07:13,955
It was-- it was our stem, Cisserus.
是——是我们的源头，西瑟勒斯。

1333
01:07:13,989 --> 01:07:16,024
She's a monster.
她是个怪物。

1334
01:07:16,057 --> 01:07:18,126
She's gonna louse it up for all of us.
她会把我们所有人都搞砸的。

1335
01:07:18,159 --> 01:07:20,629
Don't trip. We'll talk to Tepish.
别紧张。我们会和泰皮什谈谈。

1336
01:07:20,662 --> 01:07:23,098
Oh, I saw him after work
哦，我下班后见过他

1337
01:07:23,131 --> 01:07:25,000
and he said you'll be feeling better soon.
他说你很快就会感觉好些的。

1338
01:07:25,033 --> 01:07:26,534
You're just pregnant.
你只是怀孕了。

1339
01:07:26,568 --> 01:07:29,304
What?
什么？

1340
01:07:29,337 --> 01:07:31,406
I'm pregnant? We're gonna have a baby.
我怀孕了？我们要有孩子了。

1341
01:07:31,439 --> 01:07:33,141
I'm pregnant!
我怀孕了！

1342
01:07:33,174 --> 01:07:35,110
Oh, my God!
哦，我的天！

1343
01:07:35,143 --> 01:07:36,678
Oh, I can't believe this. I'm pregnant?
哦，我不敢相信。我怀孕了？

1344
01:07:36,711 --> 01:07:38,413
You want a baby?
你想要孩子吗？

1345
01:07:38,446 --> 01:07:40,282
Well...
嗯…

1346
01:07:40,315 --> 01:07:42,617
yeah.
是的。

1347
01:07:42,651 --> 01:07:45,120
I'm over 40. How many more chances am I gonna get?
我四十多岁了。我还能有多少机会？

1348
01:07:45,153 --> 01:07:46,664
And besides, I'll make a kick-ass father.
再说，我会是个超赞的爸爸。

1349
01:07:46,688 --> 01:07:48,232
All right.
好吧。

1350
01:07:48,256 --> 01:07:50,558
Forget cell phones, forget iPhones,
忘了手机，忘了iPhone，

1351
01:07:50,592 --> 01:07:53,361
forget PowerBooks, forget iPads.
忘了PowerBook，忘了iPad。

1352
01:07:53,395 --> 01:07:55,063
Yay.
耶。

1353
01:07:55,096 --> 01:07:57,699
Now I can do everything I want
现在我可以做任何我想做的事

1354
01:07:57,732 --> 01:07:59,601
with my iPad Mini.
用我的iPad Mini。

1355
01:07:59,634 --> 01:08:01,236
That looks just like your phone.
那看起来就像你的手机。

1356
01:08:01,269 --> 01:08:03,038
But it doesn't make calls.
但它不能打电话。

1357
01:08:03,071 --> 01:08:05,173
I got my tweets, I got my e-mails,
我有我的推特，我有我的邮件，

1358
01:08:05,206 --> 01:08:06,617
I got my friends, I got my alerts, I got--
我有我的朋友，我有我的提醒，我有——

1359
01:08:06,641 --> 01:08:08,543
So as the day progresses, you can read
所以随着一天过去，你可以阅读

1360
01:08:08,576 --> 01:08:11,146
thousands of unsolicited messages,
成千上万的不请自来的消息，

1361
01:08:11,179 --> 01:08:15,083
advertisements, and the mindless brain vomit of acquaintances?
广告，以及熟人们无意识的大脑呕吐物？

1362
01:08:15,116 --> 01:08:16,785
Someone sounds hormonal.
有人听起来荷尔蒙失调了。

1363
01:08:16,818 --> 01:08:18,353
Maybe you're pregnant, too!
也许你也怀孕了！

1364
01:08:18,386 --> 01:08:20,322
So annoying.
太烦人了。

1365
01:08:20,355 --> 01:08:23,024
You have to keep learning to use new crap
你必须不断学习使用新的垃圾

1366
01:08:23,058 --> 01:08:24,693
that doesn't actually do anything better
实际上并没有比旧的垃圾

1367
01:08:24,726 --> 01:08:27,195
than the old crap, which is incompatible with the new crap,
做得更好，而旧的垃圾与新的垃圾不兼容，

1368
01:08:27,228 --> 01:08:30,065
all so you can have blogs and watch fake teenagers
所有这些都是为了让你有博客和看假的青少年

1369
01:08:30,098 --> 01:08:31,766
and real housewives?
和真正的家庭主妇？

1370
01:08:31,800 --> 01:08:34,669
And it's all happening too fast
这一切发生得太快了

1371
01:08:34,703 --> 01:08:36,538
and I'm tired.
我累了。

1372
01:08:36,571 --> 01:08:40,542
I'm just sick and tired of it all.
我只是厌倦了这一切。

1373
01:08:40,575 --> 01:08:43,211
It's okay.
没关系。

1374
01:08:43,244 --> 01:08:45,180
We don't have to get the iPad Minis.
我们不必买iPad Mini。

1375
01:08:49,150 --> 01:08:50,452
No, I'm sorry...
不，我很抱歉…

1376
01:08:50,485 --> 01:08:53,321
Look. Only a couple stations, but they had Groucho Marx.
看。只有几个台，但他们有格劳乔·马克斯。

1377
01:08:53,355 --> 01:08:55,357
No, that's not Groucho.
不，那不是格劳乔。

1378
01:08:55,390 --> 01:08:57,092
Groucho was the mustache guy.
格劳乔是那个有胡子的人。

1379
01:08:57,125 --> 01:08:58,502
Yeah, he had glasses and a cigar.
是的，他戴眼镜抽雪茄。

1380
01:08:58,526 --> 01:09:00,428
Yeah, a cigar and glasses.
是的，雪茄和眼镜。

1381
01:09:00,462 --> 01:09:02,263
You'll split $25 between you. Are you ready?
你们将平分25美元。你们准备好了吗？

1382
01:09:02,297 --> 01:09:04,065
Yes. Who is buried in Grant's Tomb?
是的。谁埋在格兰特墓？

1383
01:09:04,099 --> 01:09:05,734
Were people really that stupid?
人们真的那么蠢吗？

1384
01:09:05,767 --> 01:09:08,236
No, that's what he'd ask when he felt bad
不，那是他感觉不好时会问的

1385
01:09:08,269 --> 01:09:09,671
and wanted to give 'em a few bucks.
想给他们几块钱。

1386
01:09:09,704 --> 01:09:11,373
Is Grant's Tomb in New York?
格兰特墓在纽约吗？

1387
01:09:11,406 --> 01:09:13,475
No. No. Yeah. Yeah.
不。不。是的。是的。

1388
01:09:13,508 --> 01:09:15,243
Have any of you ever been there?
你们有人去过那里吗？

1389
01:09:15,276 --> 01:09:17,212
No. No.
不。不。

1390
01:09:17,245 --> 01:09:20,081
- That's it.
- What?
- 就是它。
- 什么？

1391
01:09:20,115 --> 01:09:23,685
God, the place no New Yorker ever goes.
天哪，那个没有纽约人会去的地方。

1392
01:09:23,718 --> 01:09:26,187
Of course, Cisserus would want a monument.
当然，西瑟勒斯会想要一个纪念碑。

1393
01:09:26,221 --> 01:09:27,589
And it's got a tomb.
它还有个墓。

1394
01:09:27,622 --> 01:09:29,424
Oh, my God. You're probably right.
哦，我的天。你可能说对了。

1395
01:09:29,457 --> 01:09:31,059
Come on.
来吧。

1396
01:09:33,795 --> 01:09:35,397
Show me again. Yeah, here.
再给我看看。是的，这里。

1397
01:09:35,430 --> 01:09:37,799
I guess I totally can tell, but it's--
我想我完全能看出来，但是它——

1398
01:09:37,832 --> 01:09:39,477
it's like, I don't know. I always thought you'd be
它就像，我不知道。我一直以为你会是

1399
01:09:39,501 --> 01:09:41,236
the first one to have a baby. Is that weird?
第一个有孩子的。那很奇怪吗？

1400
01:09:41,269 --> 01:09:42,771
But now that it's happening-- Listen.
但现在它正在发生——听着。

1401
01:09:42,804 --> 01:09:46,141
You have to decide something independent of me or Joey.
你必须独立于我或乔伊做出决定。

1402
01:09:46,174 --> 01:09:49,244
This baby won't survive in your condition.
这个孩子在你的状态下无法存活。

1403
01:09:49,277 --> 01:09:51,646
If you want it, you have to turn back.
如果你想要它，你必须变回去。

1404
01:09:51,679 --> 01:09:53,214
How does that even--
那怎么——

1405
01:09:53,248 --> 01:09:55,116
Cisserus would have to be killed.
西瑟勒斯必须被杀死。

1406
01:09:55,150 --> 01:09:56,484
That's right.
没错。

1407
01:09:56,518 --> 01:09:59,654
I'd be in my '40s.
我会四十多岁。

1408
01:09:59,687 --> 01:10:01,122
But I'd be a mom.
但我会是个妈妈。

1409
01:10:02,924 --> 01:10:06,327
You'd be older, too. I know.
你也会变老。我知道。

1410
01:10:06,361 --> 01:10:07,896
I can't decide for the both of us.
我不能替我们俩做决定。

1411
01:10:07,929 --> 01:10:11,599
How do you feel about not being young anymore?
你对不再年轻有什么感觉？

1412
01:10:11,633 --> 01:10:13,134
Which part--
哪部分——

1413
01:10:13,168 --> 01:10:16,171
running around to clubs and dating idiots?
跑俱乐部和约会白痴？

1414
01:10:16,204 --> 01:10:19,140
Would be nice not to have to fake all the references.
不必伪造所有引用会很好。

1415
01:10:19,174 --> 01:10:20,575
Ugh. Like acting nostalgic over
呃。像是对

1416
01:10:20,608 --> 01:10:23,144
"Hey, Arnold" instead of "Happy Days."
《嘿，阿诺德》而不是《欢乐时光》表现怀旧。

1417
01:10:23,178 --> 01:10:25,346
Not to mention the slang, "BTW."
更不用说俚语，“BTW”。

1418
01:10:25,380 --> 01:10:27,248
And the clothes and the music.
还有衣服和音乐。

1419
01:10:27,282 --> 01:10:29,884
Staying young is getting old.
保持年轻正在变老。

1420
01:10:29,918 --> 01:10:33,221
Plus, we'll have a baby.
再说，我们会有一个孩子。

1421
01:10:35,223 --> 01:10:38,193
What are we even talking about? We can't kill Cisserus.
我们到底在说什么？我们杀不了西瑟勒斯。

1422
01:10:38,226 --> 01:10:39,828
She's lasted hundreds of years.
她活了几百年了。

1423
01:10:39,861 --> 01:10:42,330
But that's because nobody knew where she was.
但那是因为没人知道她在哪里。

1424
01:10:42,363 --> 01:10:43,398
But she's very sturdy.
但她很强壮。

1425
01:10:43,431 --> 01:10:45,733
And let's face it, we're wimps.
让我们面对现实吧，我们是懦夫。

1426
01:10:45,767 --> 01:10:49,170
Yeah, but she's sloppy. And conceited.
是的，但她很邋遢。而且自负。

1427
01:10:49,204 --> 01:10:50,672
And we'll call in the heavy-hitters.
我们会请来重量级人物。

1428
01:10:50,705 --> 01:10:52,273
Who?
谁？

1429
01:10:52,307 --> 01:10:54,242
Your future father-in-law.
你未来的岳父。

1430
01:10:56,578 --> 01:10:59,314
I just have to do one thing first.
我得先做一件事。

1431
01:10:59,347 --> 01:11:01,749
You said for a little more time, you'd do anything.
你说为了多一点时间，你什么都愿意做。

1432
01:11:01,783 --> 01:11:04,319
Did you mean it? Of course, but what can I do?
你是认真的吗？当然，但我能做什么？

1433
01:11:04,352 --> 01:11:06,321
Would you change your schedule and stay up later
你会改变你的日程安排，晚点起床

1434
01:11:06,354 --> 01:11:08,623
and promise to let her only have animals?
并保证让她只吃动物吗？

1435
01:11:08,656 --> 01:11:11,392
Now, wait a minute. Can you keep her alive?
现在，等等。你能让她活下去吗？

1436
01:11:11,426 --> 01:11:14,729
Not exactly alive. But not dead?
不完全是活着。但不是死了？

1437
01:11:14,762 --> 01:11:17,298
I can't but he can.
我不能，但他能。

1438
01:11:17,332 --> 01:11:19,501
It's up to you. Yeah.
这取决于你。是的。

1439
01:11:19,534 --> 01:11:21,769
Yeah, I can't lose her.
是的，我不能失去她。

1440
01:11:25,673 --> 01:11:28,443
I need privacy to do this.
我需要隐私来做这个。

1441
01:12:01,442 --> 01:12:03,244
Ah.
啊。

1442
01:12:45,486 --> 01:12:48,423
That's enough. It doesn't take that long.
够了。不需要那么长时间。

1443
01:12:58,967 --> 01:13:00,735
Your wife is very sweet.
你妻子很甜美。

1444
01:13:02,837 --> 01:13:05,506
Yeah. So, uh...
是的。所以，呃…

1445
01:13:05,540 --> 01:13:07,609
I am just wondering,
我只是想知道，

1446
01:13:07,642 --> 01:13:10,311
are you guys getting along, or, uh...
你们相处得好吗，或者，呃…

1447
01:13:10,345 --> 01:13:12,880
any chance of breaking up in the future?
未来有分手的可能吗？

1448
01:13:16,351 --> 01:13:17,785
Danny.
丹尼。

1449
01:13:25,526 --> 01:13:26,995
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1450
01:13:27,028 --> 01:13:29,397
You're welcome.
不客气。

1451
01:13:37,538 --> 01:13:40,508
Come on, open up.
来吧，开门。

1452
01:13:40,541 --> 01:13:42,577
Who's there? I'm a friend of your son.
谁在那儿？我是你儿子的朋友。

1453
01:13:42,610 --> 01:13:45,613
I wanna help you. You want to help me?
我想帮你。你想帮我？

1454
01:13:45,647 --> 01:13:48,349
I've got some news for you, Grandpa.
我有些消息要告诉你，爷爷。

1455
01:13:53,454 --> 01:13:55,089
Did you say Grandpa?
你说了爷爷？

1456
01:14:00,528 --> 01:14:03,898
I thought all victims turned into vampires or died.
我以为所有受害者都会变成吸血鬼或者死亡。

1457
01:14:03,931 --> 01:14:06,434
I've never heard of anyone turning back.
我从未听说过有人变回来。

1458
01:14:06,467 --> 01:14:08,469
Well, I've never known anyone firsthand.
嗯，我从未亲身认识过任何人。

1459
01:14:08,503 --> 01:14:11,005
But apparently, if you're young enough--
但显然，如果你足够年轻——

1460
01:14:11,039 --> 01:14:12,740
those are useless on a stem.
那些对源头没用。

1461
01:14:15,910 --> 01:14:20,415
Are you really sure this isn't just Joey's rebelliousness?
你真的确定这不仅仅是乔伊的叛逆吗？

1462
01:14:20,448 --> 01:14:23,017
I mean, do they seem serious?
我的意思是，他们看起来是认真的吗？

1463
01:14:23,051 --> 01:14:25,653
Well, I've never seen Stacy like this before.
嗯，我从未见过斯泰茜这样。

1464
01:14:25,687 --> 01:14:27,755
And he's so excited to be a dad.
他当爸爸那么兴奋。

1465
01:14:27,789 --> 01:14:30,525
I believe they really are in love.
我相信他们是真的相爱。

1466
01:14:30,558 --> 01:14:32,460
When did you awaken?
你是什么时候被唤醒的？

1467
01:14:32,493 --> 01:14:34,128
1841.
1841年。

1468
01:14:34,162 --> 01:14:36,464
I survived a feeding and begged her to turn me.
我从一次吸食中幸存下来，求她转化我。

1469
01:14:36,497 --> 01:14:38,599
You wanted to become a vampire?
你想成为吸血鬼？

1470
01:14:38,633 --> 01:14:41,569
It was the lesser of two infections.
这是两种感染中较轻的一种。

1471
01:14:41,602 --> 01:14:43,838
In 1840, there was an epidemic of cholera
1840年，霍乱流行

1472
01:14:43,871 --> 01:14:45,573
in lower Manhattan.
在曼哈顿下城。

1473
01:14:45,606 --> 01:14:48,443
It was a painful and degrading death.
那是一种痛苦而有辱人格的死亡。

1474
01:14:48,476 --> 01:14:51,145
My husband and sisters had all passed.
我的丈夫和姐妹都去世了。

1475
01:14:51,179 --> 01:14:54,449
But, miraculously, my children were fine.
但是，奇迹般地，我的孩子们没事。

1476
01:14:54,482 --> 01:14:58,553
Not to be indelicate, but I had digestive rumblings
恕我冒昧，但我有消化不良的咕噜声

1477
01:14:58,586 --> 01:15:00,154
that I knew were the early symptoms,
我知道那是早期症状，

1478
01:15:00,188 --> 01:15:03,057
and orphans did not fare well in those days.
而孤儿在那些日子里过得不好。

1479
01:15:03,091 --> 01:15:05,126
So did your kids survive?
所以你的孩子们幸存了吗？

1480
01:15:05,159 --> 01:15:09,163
My son lived to the ripe old age of 63.
我儿子活到了63岁高龄。

1481
01:15:09,197 --> 01:15:11,799
And my daughter married Peter Meester,
我女儿嫁给了彼得·梅斯特，

1482
01:15:11,833 --> 01:15:14,001
and lived to be 99.
活到了99岁。

1483
01:15:14,035 --> 01:15:16,037
Unprecedented at the time.
当时是前所未有的。

1484
01:15:16,070 --> 01:15:18,673
Well, not many elderly people had strong young mothers
嗯，没有多少老年人有强壮年轻的母亲

1485
01:15:18,706 --> 01:15:20,141
to look out for them.
来照顾他们。

1486
01:15:21,809 --> 01:15:24,112
After the grandchildren, it would've been hard
有了孙辈之后，会很难

1487
01:15:24,145 --> 01:15:26,114
to stay in their lives and not scare them.
留在他们生活中而不吓到他们。

1488
01:15:28,950 --> 01:15:31,219
- Did you get that?
- Got it.
- 你拿到那个了吗？
- 拿到了。

1489
01:15:31,252 --> 01:15:35,022
You know, the only surefire way is to behead her.
你知道，唯一万无一失的方法是砍掉她的头。

1490
01:15:35,056 --> 01:15:38,793
Everything else might just piss her off.
其他一切可能只会惹恼她。

1491
01:15:38,826 --> 01:15:40,762
And when Cisserus is dead,
当西瑟勒斯死了，

1492
01:15:40,795 --> 01:15:43,631
Stacy will be a normal girl.
斯泰茜会是个正常的女孩。

1493
01:15:43,664 --> 01:15:46,601
Normal for Stacy.
对斯泰茜来说是正常的。

1494
01:15:46,634 --> 01:15:49,904
But, what happens to you, then?
但是，那你怎么办？

1495
01:15:51,606 --> 01:15:53,674
I saved my kids.
我救了我的孩子们。

1496
01:15:53,708 --> 01:15:55,176
Let's go save yours.
我们去救你的吧。

1497
01:15:56,811 --> 01:15:58,846
Here you go. Here's your family tree.
给你。这是你的家谱。

1498
01:16:01,616 --> 01:16:03,217
Your living descendants.
你活着的后代。

1499
01:16:03,251 --> 01:16:06,554
A great-great-great-great grandson.
一个曾曾曾曾孙子。

1500
01:16:06,587 --> 01:16:09,924
A drug addict. Incarcerated.
一个瘾君子。被监禁。

1501
01:16:09,957 --> 01:16:14,695
Four doctors. One in Doctors Without Borders.
四个医生。一个在无国界医生组织。

1502
01:16:14,729 --> 01:16:17,165
Two professors, four teachers,
两个教授，四个老师，

1503
01:16:17,198 --> 01:16:19,200
and in the House of Representatives,
在众议院，

1504
01:16:19,233 --> 01:16:22,170
Jane Rutherford, who chairs several committees.
简·卢瑟福，主持几个委员会。

1505
01:16:22,203 --> 01:16:23,771
She looks like you.
她长得像你。

1506
01:16:25,540 --> 01:16:26,974
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1507
01:16:28,042 --> 01:16:30,678
All right, leave the guns.
好了，放下枪。

1508
01:16:30,711 --> 01:16:33,648
Bring the axes, hatchets, blades.
带上斧头，手斧，刀刃。

1509
01:16:33,681 --> 01:16:37,652
All right, let's go get this dried up bitch.
好了，我们去抓住这个干瘪的婊子。

1510
01:16:39,654 --> 01:16:41,756
Well, I don't go to those places much, either.
嗯，我也不常去那些地方。

1511
01:16:41,789 --> 01:16:44,859
But it just shows you can meet someone really nice.
但这只是表明你可以遇到真正好的人。

1512
01:16:44,892 --> 01:16:47,595
Well, I never go to those places, so...
嗯，我从不去那些地方，所以…

1513
01:16:47,628 --> 01:16:49,530
I can't believe I met you, though.
我不敢相信我遇到了你。

1514
01:16:49,564 --> 01:16:52,266
You are beautiful. You're so sweet.
你很漂亮。你真甜。

1515
01:16:53,835 --> 01:16:56,637
Would you like to sit? Oh, would I?
你想坐吗？哦，我当然想。

1516
01:16:58,573 --> 01:17:01,576
Nice here. Isn't it?
这里很好。不是吗？

1517
01:17:01,609 --> 01:17:03,911
Oh.
哦。

1518
01:17:03,945 --> 01:17:06,113
Isn't your wife worried about
你妻子不担心

1519
01:17:06,147 --> 01:17:08,049
where you are so late?
你这么晚在哪儿吗？

1520
01:17:08,082 --> 01:17:11,219
She's on a trip and what she don't know won't hurt her.
她在旅行，她不知道的事不会伤害她。

1521
01:17:13,688 --> 01:17:15,890
Aren't you a bad boy?
你不是个坏小子吗？

1522
01:17:15,923 --> 01:17:18,559
I can be very bad.
我可能非常坏。

1523
01:17:18,593 --> 01:17:21,863
So what does a dirty boy like you do for a living?
那么像你这样的坏小子靠什么谋生？

1524
01:17:21,896 --> 01:17:23,698
I'm a dentist.
我是个牙医。

1525
01:17:23,731 --> 01:17:26,601
You're a dentist?
你是牙医？

1526
01:17:26,634 --> 01:17:28,603
What a lucky break.
真是好运。

1527
01:17:28,636 --> 01:17:30,676
Because I have something I'm really concerned about.
因为我有件事真的很担心。

1528
01:17:30,705 --> 01:17:32,607
Can I show you?
我能给你看看吗？

1529
01:17:36,310 --> 01:17:40,081
I've never seen anything like that in my--
我从未见过这样的东西在我——

1530
01:17:40,114 --> 01:17:43,084
Oh, no! No!
哦，不！不！

1531
01:17:46,954 --> 01:17:49,056
Run! Get out of here!
跑！离开这里！

1532
01:17:52,393 --> 01:17:54,128
You asshole.
你这个混蛋。

1533
01:17:54,161 --> 01:17:55,830
Let's go.
我们走吧。

1534
01:18:04,972 --> 01:18:06,774
You bad girls.
你们这些坏女孩。

1535
01:18:06,807 --> 01:18:09,377
I am very disappointed in you.
我对你们很失望。

1536
01:18:09,410 --> 01:18:11,979
After all I've done for you,
在我为你们做了这么多之后，

1537
01:18:12,013 --> 01:18:15,016
this is how you pay me back?
你们就是这样回报我的？

1538
01:18:16,117 --> 01:18:18,619
Are you okay?
你还好吗？

1539
01:18:18,653 --> 01:18:20,655
Who treats their stem like this?
谁这样对待他们的源头？

1540
01:18:26,193 --> 01:18:28,095
Those needed gunpowder!
那些需要火药！

1541
01:18:37,705 --> 01:18:39,640
Duck!
蹲下！

1542
01:18:44,979 --> 01:18:46,647
Oh, my God. We did it.
哦，我的天。我们做到了。

1543
01:18:46,681 --> 01:18:49,650
No. You guys, we have to get her into the tomb.
不。你们，我们必须把她弄进墓里。

1544
01:18:49,684 --> 01:18:50,885
Help me. Okay, okay.
帮我。好的，好的。

1545
01:18:50,918 --> 01:18:53,654
Argh.
啊。

1546
01:18:53,688 --> 01:18:55,790
When did my ass get so flat?
我的屁股什么时候变得这么平了？

1547
01:18:59,760 --> 01:19:01,896
Can I just say-- ow!
我能说一句吗——嗷！

1548
01:19:06,100 --> 01:19:07,802
Wait-- what are we gonna do about the body?
等等——我们怎么处理尸体？

1549
01:19:07,835 --> 01:19:08,970
Oh, it'll die in a minute.
哦，它一分钟内就会死掉。

1550
01:19:09,003 --> 01:19:10,404
Where were you?
你去哪儿了？

1551
01:19:10,438 --> 01:19:12,239
What? You asked me to get a chainsaw.
什么？你让我去拿电锯。

1552
01:19:12,273 --> 01:19:14,275
I get halfway here and realize it needs gasoline.
我走到一半才意识到它需要汽油。

1553
01:19:14,308 --> 01:19:15,276
Do you know where to get gasoline
你知道哪里能买到汽油吗

1554
01:19:15,309 --> 01:19:16,711
at 4:00 in the morning?
在凌晨4点？

1555
01:19:16,744 --> 01:19:18,322
Why didn't you get it where you got the saw?
你为什么不在你拿锯子的地方买？

1556
01:19:18,346 --> 01:19:20,047
Because I thought you plugged them in.
因为我以为你是插电的。

1557
01:19:20,081 --> 01:19:21,315
What am I, a lumberjack?
我是什么，伐木工人？

1558
01:19:21,349 --> 01:19:23,818
In the forest, you're plugging things in?
在森林里，你是插东西的？

1559
01:19:23,851 --> 01:19:26,053
- Yes, like a hairdryer or a--
- Joey!
- 是的，像是吹风机或者一个——
- 乔伊！

1560
01:19:36,297 --> 01:19:39,834
Come on! Come on! I don't believe this.
来吧！来吧！我不敢相信这个。

1561
01:19:45,906 --> 01:19:47,675
Hurry! Hurry.
快点！快点。

1562
01:19:51,912 --> 01:19:53,714
Okay, close it...
好的，关上它…

1563
01:19:57,418 --> 01:19:58,986
Whoa. Okay, let's go.
哇哦。好的，我们走吧。

1564
01:20:04,225 --> 01:20:05,826
You feel anything?
你感觉到什么了吗？

1565
01:20:05,860 --> 01:20:07,128
No.
不。

1566
01:20:08,195 --> 01:20:09,864
Wait.
等等。

1567
01:20:25,946 --> 01:20:27,848
That's it?
就这样？

1568
01:20:27,882 --> 01:20:28,916
You've aged 20 years?
你老了20岁？

1569
01:20:28,949 --> 01:20:32,053
Well, I didn't drink, smoke, do drugs, or sunbathe.
嗯，我不喝酒，不抽烟，不吸毒，也不晒日光浴。

1570
01:20:38,959 --> 01:20:42,830
Oh, well, maybe your genes just aren't as good.
哦，嗯，也许你的基因就是没那么好。

1571
01:20:42,863 --> 01:20:45,032
But with Botox and laser resurfacing...
但是用肉毒杆菌和激光换肤…

1572
01:20:48,536 --> 01:20:50,871
Don't tell me you lied about your age.
别告诉我你谎报了年龄。

1573
01:20:50,905 --> 01:20:52,139
Oh, come on.
哦，拜托。

1574
01:20:52,173 --> 01:20:54,875
Who the hell names their kid Goody anymore?
现在谁他妈的还给孩子起名叫古蒂？

1575
01:20:57,912 --> 01:20:59,780
You won't get any older, will you?
你不会再变老了，对吧？

1576
01:20:59,814 --> 01:21:01,382
It's okay.
没关系。

1577
01:21:01,415 --> 01:21:03,451
I've been around long enough.
我活得够久了。

1578
01:21:03,484 --> 01:21:05,052
I'm tired.
我累了。

1579
01:21:06,320 --> 01:21:08,155
I should've known.
我早该知道的。

1580
01:21:08,189 --> 01:21:10,124
Every time I turned on the History Channel,
每次我打开历史频道，

1581
01:21:10,157 --> 01:21:12,093
all I saw was stuff about Hitler.
我看到的都是关于希特勒的东西。

1582
01:21:13,594 --> 01:21:16,530
Don't be sad. I was gonna go into the sun before I met you.
别难过。在我遇见你之前我就打算走进阳光里了。

1583
01:21:16,564 --> 01:21:18,799
You showed me how to have fun.
你教会了我如何找乐子。

1584
01:21:26,941 --> 01:21:28,876
Is there anything you want?
你想要什么吗？

1585
01:21:28,909 --> 01:21:30,111
Yes.
是的。

1586
01:21:30,144 --> 01:21:32,012
I don't wanna be here.
我不想在这里。

1587
01:21:32,046 --> 01:21:34,348
I want to be in the center of things.
我想在事物的中心。

1588
01:21:34,381 --> 01:21:36,150
Let's go.
我们走吧。

1589
01:21:47,428 --> 01:21:49,130
You all right?
你还好吗？

1590
01:22:01,575 --> 01:22:04,979
You all right? How do you feel?
你还好吗？你感觉怎么样？

1591
01:22:05,012 --> 01:22:06,981
Hungry.
饿了。

1592
01:22:07,014 --> 01:22:09,917
How about one of those pretzel things?
那种椒盐脆饼怎么样？

1593
01:22:09,950 --> 01:22:11,495
Joey, can you go get one of those pretzel things?
乔伊，你能去买一个那种椒盐脆饼吗？

1594
01:22:11,519 --> 01:22:13,287
Of course. Thanks.
当然。谢谢。

1595
01:22:55,396 --> 01:22:57,364
Goody. Goody.
古蒂。古蒂。

1596
01:23:12,513 --> 01:23:13,714
Oh, my God.
哦，我的天。

1597
01:25:11,265 --> 01:25:12,766
Oh!
哦！

1598
01:25:14,101 --> 01:25:15,703
Hey, I saw that.
嘿，我看到了。

1599
01:25:15,736 --> 01:25:17,638
What? She looked at me. I wasn't doing anything.
什么？她看着我。我没做什么。

1600
01:25:17,671 --> 01:25:19,206
Need I remind you that I gave you
需要我提醒你我给了你

1601
01:25:19,239 --> 01:25:20,750
the best years of my life? Best years of my life.
我生命中最好的年华吗？我生命中最好的年华。

1602
01:25:20,774 --> 01:25:23,277
Yeah, and I'm not talking five, 10 years here.
是的，我不是在说五年，十年这里。

1603
01:25:23,310 --> 01:25:24,812
We're talking infinity.
我们在说无限。

1604
01:25:24,845 --> 01:25:26,347
Do you have any idea what that's like?
你知道那是什么感觉吗？

1605
01:25:26,380 --> 01:25:28,649
I'm starting to get an idea.
我开始有点明白了。

1606
01:25:32,152 --> 01:25:34,321
All right, Goody. Watch this.
好吧，古蒂。看这个。

1607
01:25:38,492 --> 01:25:40,094
Too frightening.
太吓人了。

1608
01:25:40,127 --> 01:25:42,396
Is it too frightening?
是不是太吓人了？

1609
01:25:42,429 --> 01:25:44,231
Bleh!
哇！

1610
01:25:49,536 --> 01:25:53,340
Well, you got Grandpa that time.
嗯，你这次吓到爷爷了。

